description: This is a generic event which represents an FSP Network
Manager event log entry.
tests: $SNMPTRAPCMD FSP-NM-MIB::fspNmGenericEvent FSP-NM-MIB::id i 9999 FSP-NM-MIB::update i 1 FSP-NM-MIB::name s EXAMPLE FSP-NM-MIB::disposition i 1 FSP-NM-MIB::severity i 3 FSP-NM-MIB::impairment i 1 FSP-NM-MIB::disabled i 1 FSP-NM-MIB::neType i 1 FSP-NM-MIB::elementName s EXAMPLE FSP-NM-MIB::neIpAddress s EXAMPLE FSP-NM-MIB::entity s EXAMPLE FSP-NM-MIB::location i 0 FSP-NM-MIB::direction i 0 FSP-NM-MIB::nmsTime s EXAMPLEE FSP-NM-MIB::neTime s EXAMPLEE FSP-NM-MIB::description s EXAMPLE FSP-NM-MIB::acknowledged i 1 FSP-NM-MIB::corr i 1 FSP-NM-MIB::corrRef i 9999 FSP-NM-MIB::mtosiNeType s EXAMPLE FSP-NM-MIB::serviceName s EXAMPLE FSP-NM-MIB::customerName s EXAMPLE FSP-NM-MIB::security i 1 FSP-NM-MIB::comment s EXAMPLE FSP-NM-MIB::eventType i 0 FSP-NM-MIB::physLocation s EXAMPLE FSP-NM-MIB::entityAlias s EXAMPLE

description: Unique event identifier
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::id

description: Indicates whether it is a new event or update.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::update

description: An event acronym, e.g. LOS for Loss of signal.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::name

description: Event type.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::disposition

description: Event severity.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::severity

description: Indicates whether the alarm is potentially service affecting
(SA) or not (NSA).
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::impairment

description: Indicates whether the alarm is disabled, i.e. inhibited
(FALSE) or not (TRUTH).
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::disabled

description: Network Element Type
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::neType

description: Network element name or Line name
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::elementName

description: Network element ip address
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::neIpAddress

description: A unique name of the managed entity which the event is
related to, e.g. the Access Identifier (AID). The AID is
specific to the NE type.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::entity

description: Identifies the location associated with the particular
information, relative to entity object.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::location

description: The direction of the data flow which the event is
related to.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::direction

description: The time of detection or notification reception by the FSP
Network Manager (FSP Network Manager server time zone).
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::nmsTime

description: The time of detection by the NE (FSP Network Manager server
time zone; nmsTime if not available).
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::neTime

description: Device specific message that contain additional information
regarding the context of the event.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::description

description: Indicates whether the event has been acknowledged by an
operator or not.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::acknowledged

description: Indicates whether the event is a primary event or root cause
(PRM), or a redundant event (RDN) which is caused by another
event. It applies to alarms only.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::corr

description: If Corr=RDN this field indicates the ID of the root cause
event; otherwise it is zero. If the value is not
available -1 would be given.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::corrRef

description: The MTOSI compatible NE type string.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::mtosiNeType

description: If disposition = (alm | clr) then name of the service to
which the trap is related. Relevant only for service fault
alarms.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::serviceName

description: If disposition = (alm | clr) then name of the customer to
which the trap is related. Relevant only for service fault
alarms.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::customerName

description: Indicates whether it is a security event.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::security

description: Shows the user comment associated to an alarm.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::comment

description: Shows the event type associated with the alarm/event.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::eventType

description: Shows physical location attribute of the alarm/event.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::physLocation

description: Shows the entity alias attribute of the alarm/event.
variables.name: FSP-NM-MIB::entityAlias
